1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,669
Martha, have you met my friend?

2
00:00:02,753 --> 00:00:04,588
MARTHA: Always wanted to go to New York.

3
00:00:04,671 --> 00:00:06,548
November 1st 71930.

4
00:00:06,632 --> 00:00:08,967
You only come to Hooverville
when there's nowhere else to go.

5
00:00:09,092 --> 00:00:10,969
Men going missing, is this true?

6
00:00:11,762 --> 00:00:12,930
Laszlo?

7
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:18,101
DALEX: The Empire State Building
must be completed in time.

8
00:00:18,185 --> 00:00:20,103
-Are you trying to kill us?
-Don't argue with me!

9
00:00:20,437 --> 00:00:23,440
This human is our best option.

10
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:25,108
No!

11
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:28,278
The Final Experiment will begin.

12
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:32,449
The children of Skaro must walk again.

13
00:00:33,242 --> 00:00:34,284
What is it?

14
00:00:34,409 --> 00:00:39,831
I am a human Dalek.

15
00:01:19,079 --> 00:01:23,417
These humans will become like me.

16
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:27,588
Prepare them for hybridisation.

17
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:29,298
(PIG SLAVES SNORTING)

18
00:01:30,841 --> 00:01:32,843
MARTHA: Leave me alone. Don't you dare!

19
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:35,554
(HAPPY DAYS ARE HERE AGAIN PLAYING)

20
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:37,973
What is that sound?

21
00:01:38,265 --> 00:01:40,934
Ah, well now, that would be me.

22
00:01:41,018 --> 00:01:44,271
Hello. Surprise! Boo! Etcetera.

23
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:47,983
-Doctor?
-The enemy of the Daleks!

24
00:01:48,066 --> 00:01:50,277
-Exterminate!
-Wait!

25
00:01:52,195 --> 00:01:54,531
Well, then, a new form of Dalek.

26
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,368
Fascinating and very clever.

27
00:01:58,869 --> 00:02:02,497
The Cult of Skaro
escaped your slaughter.

28
00:02:02,956 --> 00:02:05,042
How did you end up in 19307

29
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:08,003
Emergency temporal shift.

30
00:02:08,170 --> 00:02:12,591
Oh, that must've roasted up
your power cells, eh?

31
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:17,679
Time was, four Daleks
could've conquered the world!

32
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:20,891
But instead, you're skulking away,

33
00:02:21,725 --> 00:02:24,895
hidden in the dark, experimenting.

34
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:31,109
-All of which results in you.
-I am Dalek in human form.

35
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:34,237
But what does it feel like?

36
00:02:34,363 --> 00:02:36,323
You can talk to me, Dalek Sec.

37
00:02:36,740 --> 00:02:39,076
It is Dalek Sec, isn't it,
that's your name?

38
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,203
You've got a name
and a mind of your own.

39
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:43,246
Tell me what you're thinking right now.

40
00:02:43,455 --> 00:02:48,919
I feel humanity.

41
00:02:49,670 --> 00:02:51,213
Good, that's good.

42
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:55,425
I feel everything

43
00:02:55,926 --> 00:02:58,136
we wanted from mankind,

44
00:02:58,970 --> 00:03:02,307
which is ambition,

45
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:08,021
hatred, aggression and war.

46
00:03:08,772 --> 00:03:11,733
Such a genius for war...

47
00:03:11,817 --> 00:03:14,820
-No, that's not what humanity means.
-I think it does!

48
00:03:15,904 --> 00:03:22,244
At heart, this species is so very Dalek.

49
00:03:22,327 --> 00:03:24,705
All right,
so what have you achieved, then,

50
00:03:24,788 --> 00:03:27,791
with this Final Experiment, eh? Nothing!

51
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,877
'Cause I can show you
what you're missing with this thing.

52
00:03:30,961 --> 00:03:32,421
A simple, little radio.

53
00:03:32,504 --> 00:03:35,298
What is the purpose of that device?

54
00:03:35,424 --> 00:03:36,466
Well, exactly.

55
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:38,802
It plays music.
What's the point of that?

56
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,139
Oh, with music, you can dance to it,

57
00:03:43,181 --> 00:03:44,725
sing with it,

58
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:47,644
fall in love to it.

59
00:03:48,103 --> 00:03:51,940
Unless you're a Dalek, of course.
Then it's all just noise.

60
00:03:52,023 --> 00:03:53,483
(SHRILL BUZZING)

61
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:57,988
-Run!
-Protect the hybrid!

62
00:03:58,113 --> 00:04:01,116
Protect! Protect! Protect!

63
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,082
Report status.

64
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:14,671
Pain. Pain of the flesh

65
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:19,092
like no Dalek has felt
for thousands of years.

66
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:24,181
-The Doctor has escaped!
-DALEK SEC: Then find him! Find him!

67
00:04:26,767 --> 00:04:31,313
Find the Doctor.
The prisoners must be recaptured.

68
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:36,401
Come on! Move! Move! Move! Move! Move!

69
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:41,865
-And you, Tallulah, run!
-What's happened to Laszlo?

70
00:04:57,047 --> 00:04:59,841
Come on, everyone up! Come on! Come on!

71
00:05:16,274 --> 00:05:18,527
They have ascended.

72
00:05:20,070 --> 00:05:21,696
Return to base!

73
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:32,707
Request information.
What is your opinion of Dalek Sec?

74
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:35,544
We were created to follow him.

75
00:05:36,086 --> 00:05:38,755
But you have doubts?

76
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:45,887
Affirmative.

77
00:05:49,975 --> 00:05:53,979
SOLOMON: These Daleks,
they sound like the stuff of nightmares.

78
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,480
And they want to breed?

79
00:05:55,564 --> 00:05:57,983
They're splicing themselves
on to human bodies.

80
00:05:58,066 --> 00:05:59,943
And, if I'm right, they've got
a farm of breeding stock,

81
00:06:00,026 --> 00:06:02,153
right here in Hooverville.
You've got to get everyone out.

82
00:06:02,237 --> 00:06:04,447
Hooverville's the lowest place
a man can fall.

83
00:06:04,531 --> 00:06:05,740
There's nowhere else to go.

84
00:06:05,824 --> 00:06:08,159
I'm sorry, Solomon,
you've got to scatter, go anywhere,

85
00:06:08,285 --> 00:06:10,537
get on to the railroads,
travel across state,

86
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:11,913
just get out of New York.

87
00:06:11,997 --> 00:06:14,040
There's got to be a way
to reason with these things.

88
00:06:14,165 --> 00:06:16,543
-There's not a chance.
-You ain't seen 'em, boss.

89
00:06:16,835 --> 00:06:20,297
Daleks are bad enough at any time,
but right now, they're vulnerable.

90
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,632
That makes them
more dangerous than ever.

91
00:06:22,757 --> 00:06:24,009
(SNORTING)

92
00:06:38,315 --> 00:06:42,235
-They're coming! They're coming!
-A sentry must have seen something.

93
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:46,156
They're here, I've seen them!
Monsters! They're monsters!

94
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:47,282
It's started.

95
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:50,410
We're under attack! Everyone to arms!

96
00:06:52,078 --> 00:06:53,204
I'm ready, boss.

97
00:06:53,288 --> 00:06:56,541
But all of you, find a weapon!
Use anything!

98
00:06:56,625 --> 00:07:01,212
Come back! We've got to stick together.
It's not safe out there, come back!

99
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:06,593
(SNORTING)

100
00:07:09,763 --> 00:07:11,598
WOMAN: Hurry, hurry! Come on!

101
00:07:17,938 --> 00:07:20,148
-We need to get out of the park.
-We can't.

102
00:07:20,231 --> 00:07:22,567
They're on all sides. They're driving
everyone back towards us.

103
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:25,236
-TALLULAH: We're trapped.
-Then we stand together!

104
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:27,364
Gather round! Everybody come to me!

105
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,825
You there, Jethro, Harry,
Seamus, stay together.

106
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:33,620
They can't take all of us!

107
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:43,630
If we can just hold them off
till daylight...

108
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,258
Oh, Martha,
they're just the foot soldiers.

109
00:07:52,555 --> 00:07:54,182
Oh, my God!

110
00:08:00,939 --> 00:08:03,817
-What in this world...
-It's the devil. A devil in the sky.

111
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:07,529
-God save us all, it's damnation.
-Oh, yeah? We'll see about that!

112
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:09,280
That's not gonna work.

113
00:08:09,906 --> 00:08:11,992
Establish visual contact.

114
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,122
Commence the attack.

115
00:08:18,081 --> 00:08:19,499
There's more than one of them.

116
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:22,544
(ALL SCREAMING)

117
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:47,444
The humans will surrender!

118
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:49,779
Leave them alone,
they've done nothing to you!

119
00:08:49,904 --> 00:08:52,615
We have located the Doctor.

120
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:57,620
No, Solomon, stay back!

121
00:08:57,704 --> 00:09:01,332
I'm told that I'm addressing
the Daleks. Is that right?

122
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,460
DALEK SEC: Observe humanity.

123
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:08,465
For all their faults,
they have such courage.

124
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:11,843
From what I hear, you're outcasts, too.

125
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,679
-Solomon, don't.
-Doctor, this is my township.

126
00:09:14,763 --> 00:09:17,140
SOLOMON: You will respect my authority.

127
00:09:18,683 --> 00:09:20,518
Just let me try.

128
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:29,527
Daleks, ain't we the same?
Underneath, ain't we all kin?

129
00:09:34,157 --> 00:09:36,076
"Cause you see,

130
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:39,704
I've just discovered, this past day,

131
00:09:40,205 --> 00:09:45,335
that God's universe is a thousand times
the size I thought it was.

132
00:09:46,169 --> 00:09:51,966
And that scares me. Oh, yeah,
terrifies me right down to the bone.

133
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:56,012
But surely, it's got to give me hope,

134
00:09:56,763 --> 00:09:59,933
hope that, maybe together,

135
00:10:00,642 --> 00:10:03,061
we can make a better tomorrow.

136
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,689
So I beg you now,

137
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:11,694
if you have any compassion
in your hearts,

138
00:10:12,362 --> 00:10:15,990
then you'll meet with us
and stop this fight.

139
00:10:19,119 --> 00:10:20,578
Well?

140
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:23,289
What do you say?

141
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:26,417
Exterminate.

142
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,128
(SCREAMING)

143
00:10:28,253 --> 00:10:29,879
Solomon!

144
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:33,716
No! Solomon!

145
00:10:35,051 --> 00:10:38,304
They killed him.
They just shot him on the spot.

146
00:10:39,681 --> 00:10:40,932
Daleks!

147
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,812
All right. So it's my turn.

148
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,022
Then kill me.

149
00:10:48,523 --> 00:10:51,693
Kill me, if it'll stop you
attacking these people.

150
00:10:51,776 --> 00:10:56,114
I will be the destroyer
of our greatest enemy!

151
00:10:56,406 --> 00:11:00,285
Then do it! Do it! Just do it!

152
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:01,452
Do it!

153
00:11:01,578 --> 00:11:04,998
-Exterminate.
-Stop! I command you, stop!

154
00:11:05,957 --> 00:11:09,544
I do not understand. It is the Doctor!

155
00:11:10,461 --> 00:11:17,218
-But I want him alive.
-The urge to kill is too strong.

156
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:21,347
I have decided. The Doctor must live.

157
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:23,850
And you will obey me!

158
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:26,811
I obey.

159
00:11:28,271 --> 00:11:30,982
-What's going on?
-DALEK SEC: Bring him to me.

160
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:36,613
-You will follow.
-No. You can't go.

161
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:42,202
I've got to go.
The Daleks just changed their minds,

162
00:11:42,285 --> 00:11:44,412
Daleks never change their minds.

163
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:46,372
But what about us?

164
00:11:51,961 --> 00:11:53,504
One condition.

165
00:11:54,047 --> 00:11:58,468
If I come with you,
you spare the lives of everyone here.

166
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:00,470
Do you hear me?

167
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,513
Obey the Doctor.

168
00:12:02,597 --> 00:12:08,311
Humans will be spared. Doctor, follow.

169
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:11,648
-Then I'm coming with you.
-Martha, stay here.

170
00:12:13,149 --> 00:12:15,652
Do what you do best.
People are hurt, you can help them.

171
00:12:15,818 --> 00:12:17,153
Let me go.

172
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:26,663
Oh, and can I just say

173
00:12:27,789 --> 00:12:29,499
thank you very much.

174
00:12:44,389 --> 00:12:47,767
You saved the Doctor. Why?

175
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:50,979
He's a genius

176
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:52,981
and we can use him.

177
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:56,567
The future of the Daleks
might well depend upon the Doctor.

178
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:04,492
MAN: Somebody help me!

179
00:13:07,370 --> 00:13:10,581
Here you go,
I got some more on the boil.

180
00:13:10,665 --> 00:13:12,041
Thanks.

181
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,961
You'll be all right, it's just a cut.
Try and keep it clean.

182
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:16,504
Thanks.

183
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:21,467
So what about us? What do we do now?

184
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:25,054
The Doctor gave me this.

185
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:28,433
-He must've had a reason.
-What's that for?

186
00:13:28,599 --> 00:13:31,394
It gets you into places.
Buildings and things.

187
00:13:31,561 --> 00:13:34,063
-But where?
-He must want me to go somewhere,

188
00:13:34,147 --> 00:13:35,773
but what am I supposed to do?

189
00:13:41,529 --> 00:13:43,656
Those people were defenceless!

190
00:13:43,740 --> 00:13:46,534
You only wanted me, but no,
that wasn't enough for you,

191
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:48,244
you had to start killing,

192
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,330
'cause that's the only thing
a Dalek's good for.

193
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:52,623
The deaths were wrong.

194
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,585
I'm sorry?

195
00:13:57,545 --> 00:14:00,590
That man, their leader, Solomon,

196
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:04,677
-he showed courage.
-And that's good?

197
00:14:04,969 --> 00:14:06,679
That's excellent.

198
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:11,642
Is it me, or are you just becoming
a little bit more human?

199
00:14:11,893 --> 00:14:14,604
You are the last of your kind.

200
00:14:15,271 --> 00:14:17,690
And now I am the first of mine.

201
00:14:19,317 --> 00:14:21,069
What do you want me for?

202
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:24,614
We tried everything to survive.

203
00:14:25,448 --> 00:14:28,659
When we found ourselves
stranded in this ignorant age,

204
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:33,247
first we tried
growing new Dalek embryos,

205
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,833
but their flesh was too weak.

206
00:14:35,958 --> 00:14:40,797
Yeah, I found one of your experiments
just left to die out there in the dark.

207
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,507
It forced us to conclude

208
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:46,010
what is the greatest resource
of this planet?

209
00:14:47,095 --> 00:14:48,471
Its people.

210
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,835
We stole them.

211
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:22,505
We stole human beings for our purpose.

212
00:15:24,674 --> 00:15:26,175
Look inside.

213
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:40,857
This is the true extent
of the Final Experiment.

214
00:15:40,940 --> 00:15:44,026
-Is he dead?
-Near death.

215
00:15:44,986 --> 00:15:49,782
With his mind wiped,
ready to be filled with new ideas.

216
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:54,203
-Dalek ideas.
-The human Dalek race.

217
00:15:56,873 --> 00:15:58,708
All of these people... How many?

218
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:02,795
We have caverns beyond this

219
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,381
storing more than 1,000.

220
00:16:06,757 --> 00:16:09,093
Is there any way to restore them,
to make them human again?

221
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:13,055
Everything that they were has been lost.

222
00:16:13,556 --> 00:16:14,974
So they're like shells.

223
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:17,268
You got empty human beings
ready to be converted.

224
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,520
That's gonna take
a hell of a lot of power.

225
00:16:19,604 --> 00:16:21,397
This planet
hasn't even split the atom yet.

226
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:22,773
How are you going to do it?

227
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:24,734
DALEK SEC: Open the conductor plan.

228
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:32,909
Wait a minute.

229
00:16:33,326 --> 00:16:37,914
Down in the sewers, the Daleks
mentioned this energy conductor.

230
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,208
What does that mean?

231
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:45,213
I don't know.
Maybe like a lightning conductor, or...

232
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:47,548
-Dalekanium!
-Oh!

233
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:51,469
They said the Dalekanium was in place.

234
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,429
In place where?

235
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:55,473
-Frank might know.
-Right.

236
00:16:59,602 --> 00:17:01,437
-Frank?
-Hmm?

237
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:04,148
That Mr Diagoras,
he was like some sort of fixer, yeah?

238
00:17:04,482 --> 00:17:07,693
-Get you jobs all over town?
-Yeah, he could find a profit anywhere.

239
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:11,364
-But where, though? What sort of things?
-You name it.

240
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:13,866
We're all so desperate for work,

241
00:17:13,950 --> 00:17:17,620
you'd just hope Diagoras
would pick you something good.

242
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:20,248
Building work, that pays the best.

243
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:23,626
But what sort of building work?

244
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:26,671
Mainly building that.

245
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,969
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
the Empire State Building.

246
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:35,471
We're right underneath that.
I worked that out already, thanks.

247
00:17:35,555 --> 00:17:37,723
But what,
you've hijacked the whole building?

248
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:41,352
-We needed an energy conductor.
-What for?

249
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,730
I am the genetic template.

250
00:17:45,481 --> 00:17:49,485
My altered DNA was to be administered
to each human body.

251
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:52,863
A strong enough blast of gamma radiation

252
00:17:52,947 --> 00:17:56,534
can splice the Dalek
and human genetic codes

253
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:59,704
and waken each body from its sleep.

254
00:17:59,954 --> 00:18:02,206
Gamma radiation? What...

255
00:18:03,165 --> 00:18:05,626
Oh, the sun. You're using the sun.

256
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:10,590
Soon, the greatest solar flare
for 1,000 years will hit the Earth.

257
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:14,051
Gamma radiation
will be drawn to the energy conductor.

258
00:18:14,302 --> 00:18:16,721
-And when it strikes...
-The army wakes.

259
00:18:17,722 --> 00:18:19,557
I still don't know what you need me for.

260
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:21,100
Your genius.

261
00:18:22,518 --> 00:18:25,313
Consider a pure Dalek.

262
00:18:25,855 --> 00:18:29,233
Intelligent but emotionless.

263
00:18:30,026 --> 00:18:32,069
Removing the emotions
makes you stronger.

264
00:18:32,361 --> 00:18:35,615
That's what your creator thought
all those years ago.

265
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,576
-He was wrong.
-He was what?

266
00:18:39,035 --> 00:18:41,621
It makes us lesser than our enemies.

267
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:45,374
We must return to the flesh

268
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:48,377
and also the heart.

269
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:51,255
You wouldn't be
the supreme beings any more.

270
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:55,343
-And that is good.
-That is incorrect!

271
00:18:55,426 --> 00:18:58,054
-Daleks are supreme!
-No!

272
00:18:58,137 --> 00:19:01,140
-Not any more.
-But that is our purpose!

273
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:03,142
Then our purpose is wrong!

274
00:19:03,225 --> 00:19:06,270
Where has our quest for supremacy
led us?

275
00:19:06,395 --> 00:19:10,733
To this. Hiding in the sewers
on a primitive world.

276
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:13,569
Just four of us left.

277
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:17,657
If we do not change now,

278
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:20,368
then we deserve extinction.

279
00:19:20,451 --> 00:19:23,579
So you want to change everything
that makes a Dalek a Dalek?

280
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:26,248
If you can help me.

281
00:19:27,792 --> 00:19:29,669
I've always wanted to go
to the Empire State!

282
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:31,587
I never imagined it
quite like this, though.

283
00:19:31,712 --> 00:19:33,297
Where are we headed, anyway?

284
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:35,341
The top, where they're still building.

285
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:37,885
Hey, how come those guys
just let us through?

286
00:19:37,968 --> 00:19:39,428
How does that thing work?

287
00:19:39,512 --> 00:19:43,265
Psychic paper, shows them
whatever I want them to think.

288
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:46,519
According to this, we're two engineers
and an architect.

289
00:19:46,644 --> 00:19:50,981
Your knowledge of genetic engineering
is even greater than ours.

290
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:55,152
The new race must be ready
by the time the solar flare erupts.

291
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:58,114
But you're the template. I thought
they were getting a dose of you.

292
00:19:58,197 --> 00:20:02,827
-I want to change the gene sequence.
-To make them even more human.

293
00:20:02,952 --> 00:20:07,456
Humans are the great survivors.
We need that ability.

294
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:09,208
Hold on a minute, though.

295
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:11,043
There's no way this lot
are gonna let you do it.

296
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:12,837
I am their leader.

297
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:17,133
-Oh, and that's enough for you, is it?
-Daleks must follow orders.

298
00:20:17,675 --> 00:20:21,053
Dalek Sec commands. We obey.

299
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:26,308
If you don't help me,
nothing will change.

300
00:20:26,684 --> 00:20:29,562
There's no room on Earth
for another race of people.

301
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:31,355
You have your Tardis.

302
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,483
Take us across the stars.

303
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,861
Find us a new home

304
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:41,449
and allow the new Daleks to start again.

305
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:45,828
-When's that solar flare?
-Eleven minutes.

306
00:20:47,872 --> 00:20:49,331
Right, then!

307
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:52,084
Better get to work!

308
00:20:57,548 --> 00:20:59,258
Look at this place!

309
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:01,594
Top of the world!

310
00:21:03,429 --> 00:21:05,389
Okay, now this looks good.

311
00:21:08,809 --> 00:21:10,936
Hey, look at the date.

312
00:21:11,020 --> 00:21:13,022
These designs were issued today.

313
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:14,982
They must have changed something
last minute.

314
00:21:15,107 --> 00:21:17,193
MARTHA: You mean
the Daleks changed something?

315
00:21:17,318 --> 00:21:18,694
Yeah, could be.

316
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:21,530
The ones underneath,
they're from before.

317
00:21:21,655 --> 00:21:24,950
That means whatever they changed must be
on this top sheet but not on this one.

318
00:21:25,034 --> 00:21:26,994
-We need to check one against the other.
-All right.

319
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:30,164
The height of this place.
This is amazing!

320
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:32,458
Careful! We're 100 floors up,
don't go wandering off.

321
00:21:32,541 --> 00:21:33,876
I just wanna see.

322
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,138
New York City.

323
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:50,476
If aliens had to come to Earth,

324
00:21:51,644 --> 00:21:53,938
oh, no wonder they came here.

325
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:03,155
There's no point in
chromosomal grafting, it's too erratic.

326
00:22:03,239 --> 00:22:04,573
We need to split the genome

327
00:22:04,657 --> 00:22:07,993
and force the new Dalek human sequence
right into the cortex.

328
00:22:08,077 --> 00:22:09,995
We need more chromatin solution.

329
00:22:10,079 --> 00:22:12,081
The Pig Slaves have it.

330
00:22:16,085 --> 00:22:18,587
These Pig Slaves,
what happens to them in the grand plan?

331
00:22:18,712 --> 00:22:23,509
Nothing. They're just simple beasts.
Their life span is limited.

332
00:22:23,592 --> 00:22:26,053
None survive beyond a few weeks.

333
00:22:28,931 --> 00:22:30,808
Power up the line feeds.

334
00:22:36,522 --> 00:22:39,608
Laszlo, I can't undo
what they've done to you.

335
00:22:40,317 --> 00:22:42,945
But they won't do it to anyone else.

336
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:45,072
Do you trust him?

337
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:51,579
I know that one man
can change the course of history.

338
00:22:52,955 --> 00:22:56,500
The right idea, in the right place,
at the right time, that's all it takes.

339
00:22:57,084 --> 00:22:58,836
I've got to believe it's possible.

340
00:23:04,842 --> 00:23:07,595
I'll go and keep an eye out,
make sure we're safe up here.

341
00:23:07,678 --> 00:23:11,056
-Don't want nobody butting in.
-There's a hell of a storm moving in.

342
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:14,476
I wish the Doctor was here.
He'd know what we're looking for.

343
00:23:16,687 --> 00:23:18,272
So tell me.

344
00:23:18,689 --> 00:23:20,649
Where did you and him first hook up?

345
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:22,985
It was in hospital. Sort of.

346
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:26,113
"Course, him being a doctor.

347
00:23:27,156 --> 00:23:28,741
Actually, I'm the doctor.

348
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:31,577
-Well, kind of.
-You're a physician?

349
00:23:32,828 --> 00:23:33,996
Really?

350
00:23:34,163 --> 00:23:37,333
I was training.
Still am, if I ever get back home.

351
00:23:38,292 --> 00:23:42,171
You could be doctors together.
What a partnership!

352
00:23:42,671 --> 00:23:44,340
Ah, such a shame.

353
00:23:44,798 --> 00:23:48,886
If only he wasn't so different,
you know what I mean?

354
00:23:48,969 --> 00:23:51,680
Oh, you have no idea
how different he really is.

355
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:55,017
Yeah, he's a man, sweetheart.
That's different enough.

356
00:23:59,021 --> 00:24:03,359
He had this companion a while back,
this friend.

357
00:24:04,652 --> 00:24:07,196
And ever since then,
he's been on his own.

358
00:24:07,321 --> 00:24:09,907
But you know, sometimes,
I say something, or do something,

359
00:24:10,032 --> 00:24:12,493
and he looks at me
and I just sort of think

360
00:24:16,538 --> 00:24:18,207
that he's not seeing me.

361
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:21,335
He's just remembering.

362
00:24:21,418 --> 00:24:23,545
Oh, listen, sweetheart,

363
00:24:24,713 --> 00:24:26,757
you want to get all sad,

364
00:24:26,924 --> 00:24:29,385
you want to have a contest
with me and Laszlo?

365
00:24:30,386 --> 00:24:31,929
No.

366
00:24:32,054 --> 00:24:34,181
But listen,
if the Doctor's with Laszlo now,

367
00:24:34,264 --> 00:24:36,725
there's every chance
that he could get him out.

368
00:24:36,809 --> 00:24:38,394
And then what?

369
00:24:39,186 --> 00:24:42,982
Don't talk crazy.
There's no future for me and him.

370
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:46,193
Those Dalek things took that away.

371
00:24:47,736 --> 00:24:51,031
The one good thing I had in my life
and they destroyed it.

372
00:24:55,828 --> 00:24:57,997
The line feeds are ready.

373
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:01,208
-Then it's all systems go!
-The solar flare is imminent.

374
00:25:01,709 --> 00:25:04,461
The radiation will reach Earth
in a matter of minutes.

375
00:25:04,586 --> 00:25:05,838
And we'll be ready for it.

376
00:25:05,921 --> 00:25:09,216
That compound will allow the gene bonds
to reconfigure in a brand new pattern.

377
00:25:09,299 --> 00:25:10,718
Power up!

378
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:15,097
Start the line feeds.

379
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:23,230
-There goes the gene solution.
-The life blood.

380
00:25:45,085 --> 00:25:47,296
Gotcha! Look!

381
00:25:49,882 --> 00:25:53,510
There, on the mast, those little lines,
they're new.

382
00:25:53,594 --> 00:25:55,387
They've added something, see?

383
00:25:55,471 --> 00:25:57,097
Added what?

384
00:26:01,977 --> 00:26:04,146
-Dalekanium!
-Dalekanium!

385
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:06,148
(ALARM BLARING)

386
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:07,566
What's that?

387
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:11,153
What's happening?
Is there a malfunction?

388
00:26:12,946 --> 00:26:14,031
Answer me!

389
00:26:14,114 --> 00:26:16,200
No, no, no. The gene feed!

390
00:26:16,325 --> 00:26:18,744
-They're overriding the gene feed.
-Impossible!

391
00:26:18,827 --> 00:26:20,746
They cannot disobey orders.

392
00:26:21,205 --> 00:26:25,834
The Doctor will step away
from the controls.

393
00:26:26,627 --> 00:26:28,921
Stop! You will not fire!

394
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:32,466
He is an enemy of the Daleks.

395
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,593
And so are you.

396
00:26:34,676 --> 00:26:38,764
I am your commander. I am Dalek Sec!

397
00:26:39,014 --> 00:26:44,561
-You have lost your authority.
-You are no longer a Dalek.

398
00:26:44,686 --> 00:26:46,438
What have you done?
What's going into the gene feed?

399
00:26:46,522 --> 00:26:50,484
The new bodies will be 100% Dalek.

400
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:52,820
No! You can't do this!

401
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:57,825
Pig Slaves, restrain Dalek Sec
and the Doctor.

402
00:27:00,035 --> 00:27:01,620
DALEK SEC: Release me!

403
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:05,249
I created you! I am your master!

404
00:27:06,333 --> 00:27:08,293
DALEK: Solar flare approaching!

405
00:27:08,377 --> 00:27:10,295
Prepare to intercept!

406
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:13,173
-There's the lift.
-After you.

407
00:27:16,093 --> 00:27:20,347
DALEX: The Doctor is escaping.
Stop him! Stop him!

408
00:27:20,764 --> 00:27:22,516
We've only got minutes

409
00:27:22,599 --> 00:27:23,976
before the gamma radiation
reaches the earth.

410
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:26,228
We need to get
to the top of the building.

411
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:28,480
Laszlo, what's wrong?

412
00:27:28,564 --> 00:27:30,816
Out of breath. It's nothing.

413
00:27:32,568 --> 00:27:35,404
We escaped them, Doctor,
that's all that matters.

414
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:42,744
You have betrayed me.

415
00:27:43,745 --> 00:27:46,081
You told us to imagine.

416
00:27:46,623 --> 00:27:49,501
And we imagined your irrelevance.

417
00:27:49,585 --> 00:27:54,006
I was your leader! I am Dalek Sec!

418
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:55,424
Obey me!

419
00:27:55,507 --> 00:27:56,592
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

420
00:27:57,593 --> 00:27:59,344
-Doctor!
-First floor, perfumery.

421
00:27:59,428 --> 00:28:01,889
I never thought I'd see you again!

422
00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:03,724
No stopping me.

423
00:28:04,683 --> 00:28:06,185
We've worked it out.
We know what they've done.

424
00:28:06,268 --> 00:28:08,896
There's Dalekanium on the mast and
it's good to see you, too, by the way.

425
00:28:08,979 --> 00:28:10,522
Oh, come here!

426
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:13,275
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

427
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:15,485
See, never waste time with a hug!

428
00:28:15,777 --> 00:28:17,779
-Deadlock seal, I can't stop it.
-Where's it going?

429
00:28:17,905 --> 00:28:20,324
Back down to the Daleks and they aren't
gonna leave us alone up here.

430
00:28:20,407 --> 00:28:22,618
-What's the time?
-11:15.

431
00:28:22,743 --> 00:28:24,536
Six minutes to go!
I've got to remove the Dalekanium

432
00:28:24,620 --> 00:28:26,079
before the gamma radiation hits.

433
00:28:26,163 --> 00:28:28,457
Gammon radiation? What the heck is that?

434
00:28:33,337 --> 00:28:35,172
Oh, that's high.

435
00:28:35,255 --> 00:28:37,257
That's very... Blimey, that's high.

436
00:28:37,341 --> 00:28:39,301
And we've got to go even higher.

437
00:28:39,885 --> 00:28:41,511
That's the mast, up there, look.

438
00:28:41,595 --> 00:28:44,514
There's three pieces of Dalekanium
on the base. We've got to get "em off.

439
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:45,891
That's not we, that's just me.

440
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:47,643
I'm not gonna just stand here
and watch you.

441
00:28:47,768 --> 00:28:50,062
No, you're gonna have
your hands full anyway.

442
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:52,356
I'm sorry, Martha,
but you've got to fight.

443
00:28:52,898 --> 00:28:55,817
Confirm time until solar intercept.

444
00:28:56,902 --> 00:28:59,905
Gamma strike, four minutes and counting!

445
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:37,901
(BUZZING)

446
00:29:44,866 --> 00:29:50,372
Pig Slaves will take the lift!
Find the Doctor! Kill him!

447
00:29:50,706 --> 00:29:53,292
(PIG SLAVES SNORTING)

448
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:01,383
-The lift's coming up.
-I should have brought that gun.

449
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:03,385
Tallulah, stay back. You, too, Martha.

450
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,429
If they send Pig Slaves,
they're trained to kill.

451
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:07,180
The Doctor needs me to fight,
I'm not going anywhere.

452
00:30:07,264 --> 00:30:09,057
But they're savages. I should know.

453
00:30:09,141 --> 00:30:11,768
They're trained to slit your throat
with their bare teeth.

454
00:30:13,770 --> 00:30:16,148
Laszlo, what is it?

455
00:30:16,356 --> 00:30:18,859
No, it's nothing, I'm fine.
Just leave me.

456
00:30:21,361 --> 00:30:23,572
Oh, honey, you're burning up.

457
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:26,199
What's wrong with you? Tell me!

458
00:30:26,283 --> 00:30:28,410
One man down, we ain't even started yet.

459
00:30:31,413 --> 00:30:33,206
-It's not looking good, Frank.
-No.

460
00:30:33,290 --> 00:30:34,916
We're gonna get slaughtered.

461
00:30:39,212 --> 00:30:40,672
Wait a minute.

462
00:30:41,757 --> 00:30:42,799
Lightning!

463
00:31:02,736 --> 00:31:05,822
You'll be all right, sweetheart.
Don't you worry.

464
00:31:06,865 --> 00:31:08,825
What the hell are you two clowns doing?

465
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:11,703
Even if the Doctor stops the Dalekanium,
this place is still gonna get hit.

466
00:31:11,787 --> 00:31:14,623
Great big bolt of lightning!
Electricity all down the building!

467
00:31:14,706 --> 00:31:16,750
Connect this to the lift,
and they get zapped!

468
00:31:16,833 --> 00:31:19,753
-Oh, my God, that could work!
-Then give us a hand!

469
00:31:21,630 --> 00:31:25,801
Gamma strike imminent. In 40 rels,

470
00:31:26,093 --> 00:31:28,762
39, 38,

471
00:31:28,845 --> 00:31:30,347
37...

472
00:31:44,903 --> 00:31:47,030
-TALLULAH: Is that gonna work?
-It's got to!

473
00:31:47,155 --> 00:31:49,408
I got it all piped up
to the scaffolding outside.

474
00:31:49,491 --> 00:31:50,575
Come here, Frank,
just sit in the middle.

475
00:31:50,659 --> 00:31:52,786
-Don't touch anything metal!
-FRANK: Okay.

476
00:31:54,329 --> 00:31:55,414
(SCREAMING)

477
00:31:56,373 --> 00:31:57,666
I can't!

478
00:31:57,749 --> 00:32:01,086
12, 71, 10...

479
00:32:16,643 --> 00:32:19,312
...zero! Gamma strike!

480
00:32:20,355 --> 00:32:21,481
(SCREAMING)

481
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:43,170
The army awakes.

482
00:33:14,868 --> 00:33:16,912
You did it, Martha.

483
00:33:16,995 --> 00:33:20,749
They used to be like Laszlo.
They were people.

484
00:33:21,416 --> 00:33:23,210
And I killed them.

485
00:33:23,835 --> 00:33:26,254
No. The Daleks killed them.

486
00:33:28,256 --> 00:33:29,508
Long ago.

487
00:33:31,259 --> 00:33:33,428
What about the Doctor?

488
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:43,146
You will identify.

489
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:48,652
-I am a Dalek.
-Excellent!

490
00:33:48,944 --> 00:33:51,780
Begin the invasion of Manhattan.

491
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:56,618
The population
will be converted into Daleks.

492
00:33:57,160 --> 00:34:01,998
And from this island,
we will conquer the world!

493
00:34:02,082 --> 00:34:06,670
Assume battle positions! Take arms!

494
00:34:22,936 --> 00:34:24,145
Doctor!

495
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:27,107
Doctor?

496
00:34:27,983 --> 00:34:29,734
Look what we found.

497
00:34:30,443 --> 00:34:31,945
Halfway down.

498
00:34:32,988 --> 00:34:35,031
You're getting careless.

499
00:34:36,032 --> 00:34:37,826
Oh, my head!

500
00:34:40,412 --> 00:34:41,830
Hiya.

501
00:34:42,205 --> 00:34:43,331
Hi.

502
00:34:43,415 --> 00:34:46,543
-You survived, then.
-So did you.

503
00:34:46,668 --> 00:34:48,044
Just about.

504
00:34:48,169 --> 00:34:52,632
I can't help noticing
there's Dalekanium still attached.

505
00:35:15,905 --> 00:35:20,910
War demands strategy.
I am designated Controller!

506
00:35:21,494 --> 00:35:23,413
That was to be my position.

507
00:35:23,496 --> 00:35:25,624
You are unfit!

508
00:35:25,707 --> 00:35:31,463
Connect me to the military computer.
I will coordinate all units.

509
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:34,215
DOCTOR: The Daleks will have gone
straight to a war footing.

510
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:35,467
They'll be using the sewer system.

511
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:37,302
Spreading the soldiers out
underneath Manhattan.

512
00:35:37,385 --> 00:35:40,013
-How do we stop them?
-There's only one chance.

513
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:42,140
I got in the way.

514
00:35:42,349 --> 00:35:44,934
That gamma strike
went zapping through me first.

515
00:35:45,226 --> 00:35:46,353
Yeah, but what does that mean?

516
00:35:46,436 --> 00:35:47,520
We need to draw fire.

517
00:35:47,604 --> 00:35:49,147
Before they can attack New York,
I need to face them.

518
00:35:49,230 --> 00:35:50,315
Where can I draw them out?

519
00:35:50,398 --> 00:35:51,650
Think, think, think, think, think.

520
00:35:51,733 --> 00:35:54,527
I need some sort of space, somewhere
safe, somewhere out of the way.

521
00:35:55,236 --> 00:35:57,030
-Tallulah!
-That's me, three L's and an H!

522
00:35:57,113 --> 00:35:58,448
The theatre! It's right above them!

523
00:35:58,531 --> 00:36:00,158
And what, it's gone midnight.
Can you get us inside?

524
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:02,327
-Don't see why not.
-Is there another Lift?

525
00:36:02,410 --> 00:36:04,329
We came up in the service elevator.

526
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:06,665
That'll do! Allons-y!

527
00:36:07,832 --> 00:36:09,834
DALEK: Report status!

528
00:36:09,918 --> 00:36:15,590
Maximum efficiency!
I am now ready for full-scale war!

529
00:36:16,299 --> 00:36:21,137
-Control over Dalek humans?
-Connection confirmed!

530
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:23,598
All soldiers will take heed!

531
00:36:25,058 --> 00:36:27,602
Weapons will be primed!

532
00:36:30,897 --> 00:36:33,274
This should do it. Here we go.

533
00:36:34,776 --> 00:36:38,154
There ain't nothing more creepy
than a theatre in the dark.

534
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:42,158
Listen, Doctor, I know you've got
a thing for show tunes,

535
00:36:42,283 --> 00:36:44,536
but there's a time and a place, huh?

536
00:36:45,120 --> 00:36:47,288
Laszlo? What's wrong?

537
00:36:48,623 --> 00:36:51,626
Nothing. It's just so hot.

538
00:36:52,377 --> 00:36:54,504
But it's freezing in here.

539
00:36:54,838 --> 00:36:57,006
Doctor, what's happening to him?

540
00:36:57,132 --> 00:36:58,633
Not now, Tallulah, sorry.

541
00:36:58,717 --> 00:36:59,843
What are you doing?

542
00:36:59,926 --> 00:37:01,010
If the Daleks are going to war,

543
00:37:01,136 --> 00:37:03,555
they'll want to find
their number one enemy.

544
00:37:03,638 --> 00:37:05,807
I'm just telling them where I am.

545
00:37:07,642 --> 00:37:09,811
Sonic device detected!

546
00:37:10,019 --> 00:37:15,191
-The Doctor survived!
-Find him and exterminate!

547
00:37:15,275 --> 00:37:17,694
I'm telling you to go.
Frank can take you back to Hooverville.

548
00:37:17,777 --> 00:37:19,279
And I'm telling you, I'm not going.

549
00:37:19,362 --> 00:37:20,989
Martha! That's an order!

550
00:37:21,072 --> 00:37:22,615
Who are you then, some sort of Dalek?

551
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:23,825
(CRASHING)

552
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,370
Doctor! Oh, my God!

553
00:37:31,583 --> 00:37:36,421
-Well, I guess that's them, then, huh?
-Humans with Dalek DNA?

554
00:37:36,504 --> 00:37:38,673
It's all right.
All right, just stay calm.

555
00:37:38,757 --> 00:37:40,884
-Don't antagonise them.
-But what of the Dalek masters?

556
00:37:41,009 --> 00:37:42,051
Where are they?

557
00:37:42,135 --> 00:37:46,514
Doctor located! Advance! Advance!

558
00:37:47,015 --> 00:37:49,184
(SCREAMING)

559
00:38:12,874 --> 00:38:16,878
DALEX:. The Doctor
will stand before the Daleks.

560
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:29,265
You will die, Doctor.
It's the beginning of a new age.

561
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:33,102
Planet Earth will become new Skaro!

562
00:38:33,394 --> 00:38:35,146
Oh, and what a world.

563
00:38:36,022 --> 00:38:39,776
With anything just the slightest bit
different ground into the dirt.

564
00:38:39,859 --> 00:38:42,737
That's Dalek Sec! Don't you remember?

565
00:38:42,862 --> 00:38:46,658
The cleverest Dalek ever
and look what you've done to him.

566
00:38:47,909 --> 00:38:51,120
Is that your new empire? Hmm?

567
00:38:52,372 --> 00:38:55,542
Is that the foundation
for a whole new civilisation?

568
00:38:55,959 --> 00:38:57,252
My Daleks,

569
00:38:59,754 --> 00:39:01,589
just understand this.

570
00:39:02,257 --> 00:39:05,301
If you choose death and destruction,

571
00:39:06,386 --> 00:39:09,347
then death and destruction
will choose you.

572
00:39:09,639 --> 00:39:13,351
Incorrect! We always survive.

573
00:39:13,977 --> 00:39:18,439
Now we will destroy our greatest enemy,
the Doctor.

574
00:39:18,606 --> 00:39:19,858
DALEK SEC: But he can help you.

575
00:39:19,941 --> 00:39:22,193
The Doctor must die!

576
00:39:22,652 --> 00:39:27,407
-No, I beg you, don't...
-Exterminate!

577
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:28,616
(SCREAMING)

578
00:39:35,164 --> 00:39:36,791
Your own leader.

579
00:39:36,958 --> 00:39:40,211
The only creature who might have
led you out of the darkness,

580
00:39:40,295 --> 00:39:42,255
and you destroyed him.

581
00:39:43,131 --> 00:39:45,258
Did you see what they did? Huh?

582
00:39:46,301 --> 00:39:47,844
Do you see what a Dalek really is?

583
00:39:47,969 --> 00:39:52,807
Warning! Dalek humans
show increased levels of serotonin!

584
00:39:52,974 --> 00:39:56,477
If I'm gonna die, let's give the new
boys a shot, what do you think, eh?

585
00:39:57,312 --> 00:39:59,772
The Dalek humans. Their first blood.

586
00:40:01,149 --> 00:40:03,776
Go on! Baptise them!

587
00:40:03,860 --> 00:40:06,863
Dalek humans, take aim.

588
00:40:11,826 --> 00:40:15,204
What are you waiting for?
Give the command!

589
00:40:15,288 --> 00:40:17,165
Exterminate!

590
00:40:19,167 --> 00:40:21,169
Exterminate!

591
00:40:23,296 --> 00:40:26,925
Obey! Dalek humans will obey!

592
00:40:27,008 --> 00:40:28,843
They're not firing.

593
00:40:28,927 --> 00:40:30,386
What have you done?

594
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:32,597
You will obey!

595
00:40:32,680 --> 00:40:35,350
-Exterminate!
-Why?

596
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:39,187
-Daleks do not question orders!
-But why?

597
00:40:39,312 --> 00:40:42,774
-You will stop this!
-But why?

598
00:40:42,857 --> 00:40:45,068
You must not question!

599
00:40:45,818 --> 00:40:51,950
But you are not our master.
And we... We are not Daleks.

600
00:40:52,116 --> 00:40:54,035
DOCTOR: No, you're not.

601
00:40:55,244 --> 00:40:57,205
And you never will be.

602
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:00,500
Sorry.

603
00:41:00,708 --> 00:41:02,961
I got in the way
of the lightning strike.

604
00:41:04,170 --> 00:41:06,631
Time Lord DNA got all mixed up.

605
00:41:07,507 --> 00:41:09,550
Just that little bit of freedom.

606
00:41:09,634 --> 00:41:13,930
If they will not obey,
then they must die.

607
00:41:14,347 --> 00:41:15,473
(SCREAMING)

608
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:17,016
Get down!

609
00:41:17,725 --> 00:41:19,477
Exterminate!

610
00:41:23,731 --> 00:41:25,483
Exterminate!

611
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:30,613
Destroy the hybrids!
Destroy and exterminate!

612
00:41:40,748 --> 00:41:44,419
It's all right, it's all right,
it's all right. You did it.

613
00:41:44,502 --> 00:41:45,670
You're free.

614
00:41:45,753 --> 00:41:50,758
The Dalek humans are failures/
Destruct! Destruct! Destruct!

615
00:41:50,883 --> 00:41:52,218
(BUZZING)

616
00:41:53,511 --> 00:41:54,637
No!

617
00:42:02,979 --> 00:42:07,275
-They can't, they can't, they can't!
-What happened? What was that?

618
00:42:07,859 --> 00:42:10,445
They killed them,
rather than let them live.

619
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:13,990
An entire species.

620
00:42:15,491 --> 00:42:16,909
Genocide.

621
00:42:17,368 --> 00:42:19,912
Only two of the Daleks
have been destroyed.

622
00:42:21,914 --> 00:42:24,333
One of the Dalek masters
must still be alive.

623
00:42:24,667 --> 00:42:26,127
Oh, yes.

624
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:31,299
In the whole universe,

625
00:42:34,343 --> 00:42:35,845
just one.

626
00:42:41,184 --> 00:42:45,354
-Now what?
-You will be exterminated!

627
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:48,566
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah. Just think
about it, Dalek what-was-your-name?

628
00:42:48,649 --> 00:42:50,151
Dalek Caan.

629
00:42:51,986 --> 00:42:53,404
Dalek Caan.

630
00:42:56,240 --> 00:42:59,035
Your entire species has been wiped out

631
00:43:00,661 --> 00:43:03,498
and now the Cult of Skaro
has been eradicated,

632
00:43:05,333 --> 00:43:07,001
leaving only you.

633
00:43:09,337 --> 00:43:12,465
Right now, you're facing
the only man in the universe

634
00:43:12,548 --> 00:43:14,592
who might show you some compassion.

635
00:43:18,554 --> 00:43:20,723
'Cause I've just seen one genocide.

636
00:43:22,892 --> 00:43:24,352
I won't cause another.

637
00:43:27,480 --> 00:43:28,898
Caan,

638
00:43:31,567 --> 00:43:32,944
let me help you.

639
00:43:35,696 --> 00:43:39,742
-What do you say?
-Emergency temporal shift!

640
00:43:42,370 --> 00:43:43,913
(EXCLAIMS)

641
00:43:43,996 --> 00:43:46,290
Doctor! Doctor!

642
00:43:47,416 --> 00:43:48,751
He's sick.

643
00:43:48,835 --> 00:43:49,919
(WHEEZING)

644
00:43:50,169 --> 00:43:52,421
It's okay. You're all right.

645
00:43:52,547 --> 00:43:53,881
(LASZLO GRUNTING)

646
00:43:58,678 --> 00:44:01,848
It's his heart. It's racing like mad.
I've never seen anything like it.

647
00:44:01,931 --> 00:44:03,474
TALLULAH: What is it, Doctor?

648
00:44:03,558 --> 00:44:04,809
What's the matter with him?

649
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:07,019
He says he can't breathe. What is it?

650
00:44:07,103 --> 00:44:09,397
It's time, sweetheart.

651
00:44:09,856 --> 00:44:12,733
What do you mean, "time"?
What are you talking about?

652
00:44:13,234 --> 00:44:18,030
None of the slaves survive for long.
Most of them only live for a few weeks.

653
00:44:19,699 --> 00:44:21,159
I was lucky.

654
00:44:22,577 --> 00:44:24,787
I held on 'cause I had you.

655
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:27,039
But now...

656
00:44:27,456 --> 00:44:29,125
I'm dying, Tallulah.

657
00:44:29,250 --> 00:44:32,670
No, you're not. Not now, after all this.

658
00:44:33,254 --> 00:44:35,756
Doctor, can't you do something?

659
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:40,970
Oh, Tallulah, with three L's and an H,

660
00:44:43,181 --> 00:44:46,017
just you watch me. What do I need?

661
00:44:46,100 --> 00:44:49,145
Oh, I don't know, how about
a great, big genetic laboratory?

662
00:44:49,270 --> 00:44:51,105
Oh, look! I've got one!

663
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:53,983
Laszlo, just you hold on!

664
00:44:54,066 --> 00:44:57,987
There's been too many deaths today.
Way too many people have died.

665
00:44:58,279 --> 00:45:01,240
Brand-new creatures and wise old men
and age-old enemies.

666
00:45:01,324 --> 00:45:03,951
And I'm telling you,
I'm telling you right now,

667
00:45:04,076 --> 00:45:08,956
I am not having one more death!
You got that? Not one!

668
00:45:09,790 --> 00:45:11,918
Tallulah, out of the way.

669
00:45:12,793 --> 00:45:14,003
The Doctor is in!

670
00:45:20,676 --> 00:45:24,555
Well, I talked to them and I told them
what Solomon would've said,

671
00:45:24,639 --> 00:45:26,849
and I reckon
I shamed one or two of them.

672
00:45:27,183 --> 00:45:28,893
What did they say?

673
00:45:29,518 --> 00:45:31,145
They said yes.

674
00:45:32,438 --> 00:45:34,440
They'll give you a home, Laszlo.

675
00:45:35,816 --> 00:45:39,445
I mean, don't imagine
people ain't gonna stare.

676
00:45:40,446 --> 00:45:42,823
I can't promise you'll be at peace.

677
00:45:43,616 --> 00:45:46,452
But, in the end,
that is what Hooverville is for.

678
00:45:47,370 --> 00:45:49,247
People who ain't got nowhere else.

679
00:45:50,373 --> 00:45:51,749
Thank you.

680
00:45:52,375 --> 00:45:54,669
I...I can't thank you enough.

681
00:46:01,008 --> 00:46:02,593
MARTHA: Do you reckon it's gonna work?

682
00:46:02,677 --> 00:46:04,595
-Those two?
-I don't know.

683
00:46:05,763 --> 00:46:08,099
Anywhere else in the universe,
I might worry about them.

684
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:10,601
But New York?
That's what this city's good at.

685
00:46:10,935 --> 00:46:13,938
Give me your tired, your poor,
your huddled masses

686
00:46:14,021 --> 00:46:17,108
and maybe the odd Pig Slave-Dalek
mutant hybrid, too.

687
00:46:17,233 --> 00:46:21,279
-The pig and the showgirl!
-The pig and the showgirl.

688
00:46:21,362 --> 00:46:25,533
Just proves it, I suppose.
There's someone for everyone.

689
00:46:27,451 --> 00:46:28,703
Maybe.

690
00:46:34,583 --> 00:46:37,044
I meant to say, I'm sorry.

691
00:46:37,128 --> 00:46:38,296
What for?

692
00:46:38,379 --> 00:46:41,215
Just 'cause that Dalek got away.
I know what that means to you.

693
00:46:41,299 --> 00:46:42,466
Mmm.

694
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:44,969
Do you think you'll ever see it again?

695
00:46:45,052 --> 00:46:46,387
Oh, yes.

696
00:46:52,685 --> 00:46:54,061
One day.

697
00:47:00,776 --> 00:47:04,113
Tonight, I'm going to perform a miracle.

698
00:47:05,031 --> 00:47:06,407
Something's wrong.

699
00:47:06,490 --> 00:47:10,453
I'm 76 years old and I am reborn.

700
00:47:10,745 --> 00:47:13,205
-This is a friend of mine.
-Lovely to meet you, Mrs Jones.

701
00:47:13,289 --> 00:47:14,415
Tish!

702
00:47:16,167 --> 00:47:18,127
DOCTOR: You people
are in serious danger!

703
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:20,254
You need to get out of here right now!

704
00:47:23,883 --> 00:47:25,968
No, get away from her!

705
00:47:26,469 --> 00:47:28,137
There's one more.

